    length more then 8 letters onwards: their "real" prices are multiplied by
    3,4,5... (not 4,8,16... as before).

  - Sorting of different word lists is now being handled according to your
    current locale settings. That's why it would be better if you do not
    specify language for playing as a @{" tooltype " link Startup}; better
    use your default system locale settings instead.

  - More fantabulous MUI help bubbles added :)

  - Bug fixed: merging dictionaries when no highscores table was available and
    new highscores table came with new dictionary caused trashing of this table.

  - When merging dictionaries, the new dictionary from now is tested for
    compliance to current TossWord's language.

  - Lists of player's names are from now "language sensitive" and must have
    the same extension, as current TossWord's language - say, not "Players",
    but "Players.english".

  - Installer script now preserves your existing dictionaries (if any), when
    refreshing old installation of TossWord.

