    notified  as soon as possible and the game will be aborted without saving
    dictionary to disk (it is not safe to continue game in this case anyway).
    You'd better reset your Amiga if such a disaster happens...

  - The lists of English and Russian letters are no longer loaded from the
    "Prices" file(s) - they are built-in instead. Of course, the prices
    of valid letters are still being taken from "Prices" files.

  - Bug fixed: last letters in the words were not validated during
    export operation.

  - Bug fixed: adding words to dictionary via ARexx sometimes caused
    garbage characters to be appended to new words.

  - Some internal handling of deleting of words from dictionaries
    rewritten. Now when trying to delete a word you may possibly get
    the message "Can't delete the word now. Do it later". That means,
    that the thinking process which is concurrently working the moment
    has choosen this word as a possible candidate to be put on the
    playfield and it's impossible to remove it safely. This is an
    extremely rare case though.

  - Now you can choose the program's behaviour when you put an unknown
    word on the playfield. In earlier versions it was immediately accepted
    (only for Russian language it was rougly checked to see if it MAY be
    Russian word or not). Now you may choose between old behavoir, or
    ask the player whether he (she) is sure that this word exists, or
    reject it entirely.

1.15

  - @{" Cut words " link Cut} menu option added.

  - bug fixed: you couldn't @{" import " link Import} words longer then current
    field size. Now words can be up to 40 characters long.

  - bug fixed - after deletetion of words sometimes it was reported that
    dictionary was corrupted, even though it wasn't.

  - a lot of new Russian words were added to Russian dictionary.

1.16

  - bug fixed: if Amiga ran out of time while thinking about her move,
    then the turn to move didn't go to next player. Can't understand,
    how this bug could exist for such a long time :((.

  - buf fixed: if you query for number of variants pressing F1 or F2 and
    your time has expired (and Amiga still couldn't calculate all the
    variants), then you were told abount the variants at other player's
    time.

1.17

  - fixed ugly and silly bug, which caused Enforcer hits (write of byte 0 to
    $0000) when "Who's turn" option in speech settings was enabled.

  - bug fixed: it could be potentially possible in some cases that background
    thinking wasn't really running in the background and human player,
    therefore, had to wait until Amiga will calculate his variants before
    making actual move.

  - bug fixed: when Amiga puts more then 2 words at oncce (rather rare case :),
    you could possibly (even more rare case) get the message "Cx Error #6".

  - when you drag letters to playfield and occasionally click somewhere
    in the outside area of the field, the last letter won't be removed
    to your bank as it happened before.

  - bug fixed: after playing a game the general settings field of settings
    window remained disabled.

  - fixed funny bug which caused crash after program exit under MUI 3.2
    (not MUI 3.1). Can tell details to Stefan Stuntz only :)

  - pause screen option is redone from scratch.

  - some minor rules of the game were changed: maximum 10 points are given
    now for unknown words and writing of highscores was changed also.

  - bug fixed: in some rare cases Amiga could not see "good moves", when
    several words were formed simultaneously.

  - from now you can't play game if your dictionary contains less then 5000
    words (20.000 words for Russian language).

  - new tooltypes POPUP_SETTINGS and ...PLAYERS are introduced.

  - parsing of player's names during their input in setting's window became
    more intellectual :)

  - background thinking is now switched off temporarily when player
    presses the ESC key in order to move back some of his letters from
    the field. This was done in order to speed up this process on slow
    machines.

1.18

  - since now Amiga will speak the word it puts on the playfield (of
    course, if this option is enabled) even if it was putting the word
    "in a hurry" due to shortage of time. The (somehow changed) sound of
    moving letters is also produced in this case.

  - bug fixed - some bizarre movements of letters happened if you denied
    computer move while the game was paused. Now you must switch pause off
    and then do whatever you want.

  - bug fixed - human player's time of thinking sometimes could be
    calculated incorrectly while forming of "speed of earning points"
    parameter for the table of highscores.

1.19

  - deutsch language is now available.

  - the @{" zipping " link Zip} of letters in player's banks is
    introduced. You can reirganise the order of letters in your bank
    as well.

  - tooltype "LANGUAGE" doesn't work anymore. It is not possible since now
    to play not in your system default language. Users usually got mixed
    up while handling user interface and the game itself in different
    languages. So, I decided to simplify it all radically :)

  - since now you may play TossWord on non-AGA Amigas, which are capable
    of displayin 64-coloured screens in non-EHB and non-HAM mode; activate
    @{" USE_BOBS " link Startup} tooltype and everything will be OK (I
    hope).

  - you can now get letters back from trashcan if you've decided to make
    a move instead of changing letters - just put the letter to playfield
    or simply press "Esc" key.

  - bug fixed - unregistered players got the preferences window with some
    field looking like enabled ones during the game time (fields such
    "player time" and "game time"). Couldn't properly test it, because
    it happened somehow that I'm a registered player myself... :)

  - installer script was enhanced a little bit.

