@node FAQ "Frequently asked questions"

                    Frequently asked questions

1. Why isn't it possible to put several words in different parts of the
   playfield at the same time?

   If you could do that, then it would be often more convenient to  put  several
   short  words instead of one beautiful long word. The game would lost a lot of
   it's flavour in this case. Pragmatism is not the main goal of TossWord.

2. Are there any similiar games written for other computer platforms?

   The programmer from Saint-Petersburg Oleg Kozlov made Macintosh version
   of TossWord.

3. After pressing the 'Esc' key while dragging a letter, this letter suddenly
   gets "duplicated" until I move a mouse pointer or press a mousebutton.
   Is this a bug?

   It's not a bug of TossWord - look at @{" System needed " ling Requirements } chapter.

